</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="61" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1435,151,320]" box="[199,1115,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,260,284]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Greek “lechr-” referring to the slight sidewall compression.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1435,151,320]" box="[199,1435,295,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,455,295,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">Locality and horizon.</emphasis>
Huangbanjigou Village, Beipiao City, Liaoning Province, 
<collectingCountry box="[1112,1183,295,319]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="61">China</collectingCountry>
; the Early Cretaceous.
</paragraph>
